Jul 27 2008 	There are better places to Stay	Its been 3 yrs since we stayed at Springfield but reading some of these reviews it seems nothing has changed. I still have memories of our less than impressive stay there. When we arrived during the day the man at the counter couldnt even bother looking at us and smiling. Kept his head down and was less than helpful with any questions I asked. Couldnt even muster a 'hello' or 'welcome' when we arrived. The room was adequate but very outdated. The toilet however was awful. Seat was broken, water leaking. They said they'd fix the problem but never did. So every time we sat on the loo the seat fell to the side. Not good for a female thats for sure! No lifts so we had to carry our suitcases up about 4 flights of narrow stairs. Breakfast was nice but again the man doing the cooking was rather rude. This was not the same man as in reception so it tells you something about their staff. We travelled to Windsor for a few days and asked before booking if we could leave some luggage at the hotel as we intended to stay for a few more days on our return. This was confirmed as fine however the same cook (I assume was the manager) argued about this with the same staff member. It was a rediculous scene. If we could of stayed somewhere else we most certainly would of. On our next visit we will definitely not stay at this b &amp; b.	
