Aug 23 2006 	Great Location But.....	This is a fantastic location and you get what you pay for, but be aware of a few problems we encountered:We had 3 rooms for 3 nights, there is no lift so if you are on the top floor be prepared to lug your bags up a lot of stairs. There is no air-con, which worked out OK. The toilet seat in one room was broken off, the timber surround around the shower fell off in another room, the bifold shower door was broken in two in our third room. This property could do with some maintenance. The breakfast was very good considering the cost.Our biggest problem was that the hotel staff showed people through the hotel - in our room while we were out!This hotel is located in a long street which is nothing but hotel properties. I'm sure there is something in the same location that is a better quality.	
Mar 25 2006	A comfortable stay	I must praise the Springfield Hotel where i stayed for 4 nights. It is a B+B hotel. The staff were friendly. The breakfast was very good with excellent sausages. The room was warm, but not too warm, with a lovely ensuite shower. TV had the 5 UK channels. Beds were comfortable and clean, and were made up each day. Any towels used were changed daily. Location was very easy and quick for access to the tube at Paddington. Check out is 11am but i had some time to kill before i had to go for my train and i sat in the reception sitting room watching the large TV, very comfortable. The only downside was one that they can't help - the traffic noise. Sussex Gardens can be a noisy road, but the same would be true for any of the many B&amp;Bs on this road. Thumbs up.	
