Jul 1 2005	Good Location but.............	Stayed here for one night, to go to a music festival in Hyde Park - very good area and central location. However, we encountered a problem with our booking upon arrival, and found the staff to be unfriendly. Our room was in need of refurbishment and was quite dark. The shower was rusted, and we could not get any hot water from the taps. On the morning of our stay it rained and their was a leak from the ceiling onto our bed - nice!! The breakfast wasn't up to much either. Would not stay here again, and would not recommend it until it is refurbished. If you want to stay in this area, I would recommend the Hyde Park Radnor Hotel just around the corner - excellent, but book early.	
Apr 12 2005	For what it is a great bargain in a great location	We spent 8 nights at the Springfield, using it as home base for a really great London (and Bath and Paris) exploration vacation. Location was great for us, just two blocks from Paddington (tube, National Rail, Heathrow Express; bus stops galore).It's a small, family-owned place, no elevator, no A/C. Rooms are small by American standards, but completely serviceable and clean. A small TV and a tacked-on toilet/shower combo built in to one side. Some street noise, some adjacent room noise, but nothing we couldn't live with for 65 GBP/night.The place grew on us. We particularly liked breakfast -- traditional English breakfast included in the tariff, and it was very good, indeed. Dining room is in the &quot;basement,&quot; appeared recently remodeled; clean; individual service from the owners themselves. No other meals served.Hotel puts you in walking distance to Kensington area, but better yet, at just two minutes to Paddington, buy a week's unlimited Zone 1 transit pass and you'll find nearly everything you want to see just a short bus or tube ride away. Take the Heathrow Express to and from Paddington; well worth the fare.Overall, the Springfield ain't the Plaza. Don't go there for luxury. But as a place to rest between museums and shops and day trips, it does just fine.	
